==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|sleen}}, {{m|enm|slayn}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|slēan||to strike, beat, smite, stamp, forge, sting, slay, kill, impact}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*slahaną||to fight, strike, kill}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*slak-||to hit, strike, throw}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|slaan||to beat, hit, strike}}, {{cog|nds|slaan||hit, strike}}, {{cog|de|schlagen||to beat, hit, strike}}, {{etyl|da|-}}, {{etyl|no|-}} and {{cog|sv|slå||to knock, beat, strike}}, {{cog|is|slá||to strike}}. Related to {{l|en|slaughter}}, {{l|en|onslaught}}.

